ðŸ” Key Insights (Data-Driven)
-> Overall attrition rate is 16.12%, indicating moderate employee turnover.
-> Attrition is highest in Sales and Research & Development departments.
-> Employees with 0â€“2 years of tenure show the highest attrition, highlighting early-stage retention challenges.
-> Certain job roles such as Laboratory Technician, Sales Executive, and Research Scientist experience higher attrition.
-> Employees who left the organization have a lower average monthly income compared to those who stayed.
-> Job satisfaction and work-life balance show limited direct correlation with attrition in this dataset, suggesting other factors play a stronger role.

ðŸ’¡ Business Recommendations
-> Improve onboarding and mentoring programs for new hires
-> Review compensation structures for high-attrition roles
-> Introduce work-life balance initiatives to reduce burnout
-> Implement targeted retention strategies for critical job roles
